OL,6,FNo attempt is made to bring the
OL,7,Fviewer into the programme about to
OL,8,Fstart or whet their appetite for the
OL,9,Fnext one.
OL,11,FOn a typical day, some identical
OL,12,Flinks are heard two or three times.
OL,14,FThere's nothing wrong with any of the
OL,15,Findividual links ` there are only so
OL,16,Fmany ways that even the most
OL,17,Fimaginative announcer can introduce
OL,18,Fthe third episode in a row of The
OL,19,FSimpsons ` but it does start to call
OL,20,Fthe purpose of announcers into
OL,21,Fquestion.
OL,3,CThe slippery slope of pre-recorded
OL,4,Ccontinuity announcements
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/6
